  "prompt": "What are some of the cool features on Google now?",
  "response": "As of the most recent updates, Google offers a variety of cool and useful features across its ecosystem. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **Google Assistant**: An AI-powered virtual assistant that can perform tasks, answer questions, control smart home devices, set reminders, and more through voice commands.\n\n2. **Google Lens**: An image recognition technology that allows users to search for information, translate text, identify objects, and interact with the world around them using their smartphone camera.\n\n3. **Google Photos**: Offers smart photo organization, advanced search capabilities, automatic backups, and powerful editing tools, including AI-powered enhancements.\n\n4. **Google Maps**: Provides real-time traffic updates, turn-by-turn navigation, local business information, Street View, indoor maps for large venues, and personalized recommendations.\n\n5. **Google Workspace**: A suite of productivity tools including Gmail, Google Drive, Google Docs, Sheets, Slides, Meet, and Calendar, offering seamless collaboration and integration.\n\n6. **Discover**: A personalized news feed on the Google app that surfaces content based on your interests and search history.\n\n7. **Live Caption**: Automatically generates captions for any media playing on your device, including videos, podcasts, and voice messages.\n\n8. **Google Stadia**: A cloud gaming service that allows users to stream and play high-quality video games without the need for expensive hardware.\n\n9. **Smart Reply and Smart Compose**: These features in Gmail and Google Docs suggest responses and help complete sentences using machine learning.\n\n10. **Google Home**: The app and associated smart speakers and displays enable users to control smart home devices, stream media, and interact with Google Assistant.\n\n11. **Enhanced Privacy Controls**: Google offers robust privacy settings, including options to auto-delete activity data, manage ad personalization, and control data sharing.\n\n12. **Digital Wellbeing Tools**: Features like app timers, focus mode, and bedtime mode help users manage screen time and reduce distractions.\n\n13. **Google Fit**: A health-tracking app that integrates with various fitness devices and provides insights into your physical activity and wellness.\n\nThese features demonstrate Google's commitment to integrating AI and machine learning into its services to enhance user experience and productivity.",
